"{\"uid\": \"inews.co.uk-sport-olympics-paris-2024-olympics-opening-ceremony-timings-watch-3188771\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"IMPARTIAL NEWS + INTELLIGENT DEBATE  Account  This summer's Games will kick-off with the first opening ceremony outside of a closed stadium  TheParis 2024 Olympicsbegins on Friday 26 July ahead of 16 days of elite sport across 32 disciplines.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 242, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games have been mired in controversy before they have officially started, fromCharlotte Dujardin's withdrawalto theArgentina vs Morocco footballmatch taking four hours due to fan unrest.\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 434, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9982943413119378, \"rank\": 0.0008912600498979159, \"text\": \"Morocco\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The formal start is Friday's opening ceremony, which will be the first to take place outside a closed stadium.\", \"from\": 436, \"to\": 546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's everything you need to know.\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Paris 2024 opening ceremony will take place along a 6km stretch of the River Seine, rather than in a stadium as expected.\", \"from\": 585, \"to\": 710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.897094910537993e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 660, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A fleet of 160 boats, 94 of them carrying athletes, will begin at Austerlitz Bridge and finish at Trocadero, outside the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 778, \"end\": 795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Austerlitz Bridge\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 810, \"end\": 819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trocadero\", \"score\": 0.9881396565994764, \"rank\": 0.012002694883325043, \"text\": \"Trocadero\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trocadero\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Trocadero\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 10,000 athletes representing 206 countries will participate on a river tour of Parisian landmarks, including Notre Dame cathedral and Pont Neuf.\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 1002, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 1001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.270563880203057e-33, \"text\": \"Pont Neuf\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_Neuf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony will also include French president Emmanuel Macron officially opening the Games and the lighting of the Olympic cauldron with theOlympic flame.\", \"from\": 1004, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1035, \"end\": 1051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French president\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Greece will be the first nation introduced during the ceremony, followed by the Refugee Olympic Team.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1162, \"end\": 1168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999989226818234, \"rank\": 5.527576760773258e-07, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB's joint flag bearers are diverTom Daleyand rower Helen Glover, who have won three gold medals between them at previous Games.\", \"from\": 1265, \"to\": 1398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1265, \"end\": 1272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.999809257925841, \"rank\": 0.00014763458677028373, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 1322, \"end\": 1334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553497992, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Much of the ceremony has been kept a secret, with 326,000 tickets sold to those who will line the Seine to watch.\", \"from\": 1400, \"to\": 1513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1498, \"end\": 1503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1813866497083682e-16, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd like to show France in all its diversity,\\\" said Thomas Jolly, the ceremony's artistic director.\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1615, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1533, \"end\": 1539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9993121822677293, \"rank\": 0.00042477357172822627, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1568, \"end\": 1574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"score\": 0.7355618411214557, \"rank\": 0.34191189736123756, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clarence_Thomas\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Illustrate the richness and plurality shaped by its history, which has been influenced and inspired by the diverse cultures that have passed through it, while itself serving as a source of inspiration.\\\"\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony for Paris 2024 will start at 6.30pm BST on Friday 26 July.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1847, \"end\": 1857, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.897094910537993e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1879, \"end\": 1882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 0.9999984516712793, \"rank\": 1.5483311812628945e-06, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games will officially be launched at 7.24pm BST.\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 1955, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1951, \"end\": 1954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 0.9999984516712793, \"rank\": 1.5483311812628945e-06, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the UK, the opening ceremony is available to watch onBBC and Discovery+.\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1964, \"end\": 1966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9981412553896524, \"rank\": 0.0018621811024637355, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"BBC coverage will begin at 5.45pm BST on BBC One, BBC iPlayer and BBC Sport website and app.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2034, \"end\": 2037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"score\": 0.9671400463107711, \"rank\": 0.016551201720378828, \"text\": \"BBC\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC\"}, {\"begin\": 2068, \"end\": 2071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"score\": 0.9999984516712793, \"rank\": 1.5483311812628945e-06, \"text\": \"BST\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Summer_Time\"}, {\"begin\": 2100, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Sport\", \"score\": 0.9978437187942917, \"rank\": 0.0019224048358705208, \"text\": \"BBC Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\":